f=Engineering/quinn/custom/test-strategy/assets/release-gate-matrix.md · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=Which test tiers change pass before ships. Co-owned dev quinn; changes matrix ADRs. Numeric floors come config (`coverage_floors`) matrix defines WHICH tiers, config defines MUCH. **Tiers:** unit integration end-to-end (browser evidence browser-verification) targeted regression (from regression-map, fragile area touched) security pass (aegis, dev's review routing) · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Change type \| U \| I \| E \| R \| S \| Notes \| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Feature (new surface) \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✓ critical flows \| if fragile area touched \| if new external surface/auth \| \| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Bug fix \| ✓ (incl. a test that fails without the fix) \| ✓ if cross-module \| if user-facing flow \| ✓ for the broken area (new map entry) \| if security-adjacent \| The fix's test IS the regression entry \| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Refactor (no behavior change) \| ✓ existing green \| ✓ existing green \| smoke \| if fragile area touched \| — \| New tests not required; deleted tests are \| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Config / dependency change \| — \| ✓ affected paths \| smoke \| if fragile area touched \| ✓ if dep is security-relevant \| Lockfile diffs reviewed \| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Data-adjacent (schema, migration scripts) \| ✓ \| ✓ with migration applied to test DB \| — \| ✓ \| ✓ \| Script itself is operator-run (Rail 3) \| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Security-adjacent (auth, input handling, secrets) \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✓ auth flows \| ✓ \| ✓ mandatory \| aegis verdict required \| · h1:Release-Gate Matrix [business name]=\| Hotfix (emergency) \| ✓ minimal \| — pre-ship \| smoke \| — pre-ship \| if security-adjacent \| Full tiers within <FILL_IN> hours post-ship, logged as debt \| · h2:Config-bound values (operator sets; quinn never invents rule 0.5)=`coverage_floors`: per-tier minimum coverage touched code `<FILL_IN>`, `critical_flows`: E2E-mandatory user journeys `<FILL_IN>`, `hotfix_completion_window`: hours complete deferred tiers `<FILL_IN>`